I have one of its staff members right here, standing in front of me without even putting up any defenses?! I could force her to talk right here and maybe even get away with… Well, she probably has something up her sleeve if she's a project staff member. I know you and your associates have this whole thing with not giving out information, but I'd rather ask than not."

*(All for the free exchange of information, but only answers one of my questions, hm?)* "How would I go about getting there, though?
She groans in annoyance. “Not you, sorry. Search isn’t going well. Uh, buy a plane ticket? Did they give you Earth currency?”

“No real sense in feedback. There certainly won’t be The Antarctica Project 2 to work on. Not exactly going to be a yearly event.”

She takes a sip from a hip flask.

“I’m pretty sure at least one of the heads of the project is gonna wind up dead, so your suggestion won’t do too much for self improvement. I’m here to hear you out, I guess, but you’re not making a compelling case by focusing on the most benign part of it all. I mean, doesn’t everyone want to be someone they’re not? I wished I could look different ever since I was little.”

She looks right at you, finally shedding her lazy mannerisms and making direct eye contact.

“But that’s wrong. This body is a vessel of flesh to impart my impact on the world. No more, no less. I’d discard it myself if it became a hindrance and I had the means to. And your situation isn’t even that permanent.”

Finally, their expression resolves into not one of anger, but concern. "I think… you should have more concern for your own body."
They swallow. "Sure, I can understand some part of what you're saying. I certainly can't reject the idea of seeing your own personhood as a tool to use for leaving an impact on the world. After all, what do you think the explosives are for…?" Something dark flashes across Horatius's eyes. "But we all have to make little sacrifices to ourselves. We all have that one thing that we just need to sustain our happiness, keep ourselves sane, even if it's inconsequential to our goals. And for me… it's this body." They begin to clutch at their own body, as if they're trying to hug themself. "I know it's irrational…! I know I'm just denying what I really am! But you say everyone wants to be someone they're not? Well, that's what I've already become…! This body is my one masterpiece in this world, the one thing I've allowed myself to have. I can't just let it go for someone else… I can't just let it go to waste… I can't let myself lose my one act of defiance for some worthless project…" They shudder and retreat further into themselves for a second, before realizing how they look to the other person in the room.
Horatius straightens themself out. "I don't believe your 'defense' either. If you weren't involved with the project anymore, you wouldn't care about tracking me down and directing me to my destination, or even have the ability to." They shrug. "But you've given me helpful advice, and you don't seem to be getting in my way, so it doesn't really matter."

She shrugs. “I checked out of curiosity. I guess they went with the DC location? That’s one hell of a gamble, given how the USA feels about all of this. I’d been meaning to snoop around our principal regardless of your showing up. To no avail, I guess. But no meaningful physical records either…? This man doesn’t exist…”

She shakes her head. “I guess I can’t expect others to have come to the same conclusions I have. Especially when it took decades even for me. Even if it involved shedding the relevance of my physical self, I’ve also crafted an incarnation of my existence I can be proud of. I’d be very particular about someone else having a say in that.”

She looks down.

“I’m not going to assist you in a suicide bombing, or whatever the hell you’re implying. But I’ll see if I can leverage my remaining access to the PDA systems to give you an advantage of some kind. In exchange… could you not tell Klaud we met? It’d make work awkward… and when it comes to that, I want to explain who I am myself.”
